      "content": "```python\ndef sort_orders(orders):\n    # The primary sort key is the first element (priority) in ascending order.\n    # The secondary sort key is the second element (timestamp) in descending order.\n    # The tertiary sort key is the third element (volume) in ascending order.\n    return sorted(orders, key=lambda x: (x[0], -x[1], x[2]))\n\n# Verification tests (as provided)\nassert sort_orders([(10, 0.5, 100), (5, 0.1, 50), (10, 0.2, 20)]) == [(5, 0.1, 50), (10, 0.2, 20), (10, 0.5, 100)]\nassert sort_orders([(1, 0.9, 10), (1, 0.8, 10)]) == [(1, 0.8, 10), (1, 0.9, 10)]\n```\nThis implementation uses Python's `sorted` function with",
